        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-06-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="175" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/6–3047: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ward</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mukden</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-06-30">June 30,
                            1947</date>.<lb/>[Received June 30—5:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>121. Special press release, June 30, states Nationalist troops moving northwards
                    from Mukden reached Ssupingkai at 9 a.m. today and joined forces with besieged
                    garrison in southwestern suburb of city.</p>
                <p>Sent Nanking as 207, repeated Department as 121 and Changchun as 101.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ward</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
